      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Our suspended hydronic ceiling tiles are modular and versatile. They are capable of both <strong>heating and cooling</strong> and are designed to accept a range of finishing surfaces. They are easy to install and simple to operate.
      </p>
      <p>Each tile delivers three functions in one:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>An insulative barrier</strong> — directly opposite to where the conditioning occurs</li>
        <li><strong>A highly responsive conditioning system</strong> — embedded within the tile itself</li>
        <li><strong>A finished architectural surface</strong> — providing the desired ceiling appearance</li>
      </ol>
      <p>This three-in-one design is what makes the system cost-effective.</p>

      <h2>Why Radiant Ceiling Systems?</h2>
      <p>
        The human body exchanges energy with its environment through three mechanisms: <strong>radiation</strong>, <strong>convection</strong>, and <strong>exhalation</strong> (breathing). All three work together to establish thermal comfort.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Radiant transfer has the greatest impact on comfort.</strong> Radiant systems are the most effective form of conditioning because they deliver both radiant and convective energy transfer simultaneously. They are healthier, more comfortable, and operate at roughly <strong>one-third the cost</strong> of conventional systems.
      </p>
      <p>We install our system on the ceiling because:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The ceiling offers an <strong>uninterrupted radiant surface</strong> — no furniture or foot traffic in the way</li>
        <li>It <strong>doesn't activate dust</strong> that accumulates on floors</li>
        <li>It is far more <strong>hygienic</strong> than floor conditioning or forced-air systems</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Heating and cooling</strong> in a single system</li>
        <li><strong>Multiple finishing options</strong> — choose the surface that suits your interior</li>
        <li><strong>Standard size: 600 × 1200mm</strong> — fits standard Australian suspended ceiling grids</li>
        <li><strong>Modular components</strong> — easy to install, modify, and maintain</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>System Components</h2>
      <p>Our hydronic system uses modular, low-voltage components:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Circulation pumps:</strong> 40–85W variable speed, 24V DC (each pump serves 20–40m²)</li>
        <li><strong>Switching actuators:</strong> 24V DC for hot and cold tank selection</li>
        <li><strong>Mixing valve:</strong> 24V DC with flow meter and supply temperature sensor</li>
        <li><strong>Pressure tanks:</strong> 2 litre</li>
        <li><strong>Piping:</strong> PPR with brass fittings</li>
      </ul>
      <p><em>Note: The control system is separate to the hardware listed above.</em></p>

      <p>
        <a href="/contact">Request a free consultation</a> to learn how hydronic ceiling panels can work in your space.
      </p>
